{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PropertyHint\/flags"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Hints that an integer property is a bitmask with named bit flags."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PropertyHint"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"flags"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The hint string is a comma separated list of names such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Bit0,Bit1,Bit2,Bit3\""},{"type":"text","text":". Whitespaces are "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" removed from either end of a name. The first name in the list has value 1, the next 2, then 4, 8, 16 and so on. Explicit values can also be specified by appending "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":integer"},{"text":" to the name, e.g. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"A:4,B:8,C:16\""},{"type":"text","text":". You can also combine several flags ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"A:4,B:8,AB:12,C:16\""},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A flag value must be at least ","type":"text"},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and at most "},{"code":"2 ** 32 - 1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike ``PropertyHint\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enum```, the previous explicit value is not taken into account. For the hint "},{"text":"“A:16,B,C”`, A is 16, B is 2, C is 4.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/propertyhint\/flags"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot12PropertyHintO5flagsyA2CmF","roleHeading":"Case","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"flags","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"case","title":"PropertyHint.flags"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/PropertyHint":{"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PropertyHint"}],"title":"PropertyHint","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/propertyhint","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PropertyHint","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PropertyHint","kind":"symbol","abstract":[]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","abstract":[{"text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/PropertyHint/flags":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/propertyhint\/flags","title":"PropertyHint.flags","abstract":[{"text":"Hints that an integer property is a bitmask with named bit flags.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"flags"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PropertyHint\/flags"}}}